parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's tendency to lean to the right (passenger side) can increase the risk of rollover, especially during left-hand turns, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle leans to the right
excessive body roll during left turns
feels more stable during right turns
and may roll over in certain circumstances.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Erroneous Automatic Emergency Braking System Activation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected activation of the automatic emergency braking system can cause the vehicle to abruptly stop, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops without warning
the cruise control fails to operate correctly
the vehicle stops abruptly while driving at high speeds.
